\end{align*}
is compact for any $\vPsi^*\succ 0$ since it is bounded and closed by the virtue of the Lemma and continuity of $\ell$, respectively.
The existence of a maximum follows from the extreme value theorem by the continuity of $\ell$. A stationary point exists due to Rolle's theorem and the differentiability of $\ell$.

Next, we prove the uniqueness of the maximum.
